# Frontend Development Rules - Naija News Hub

## Development Philosophy
- Create a responsive, user-friendly interface
- Follow modern web development best practices
- Ensure accessibility and performance
- Maintain consistent styling and branding
- Implement proper error handling and loading states

## Code Style and Structure

### File and Directory Naming
- Use kebab-case for frontend files and directories
  - ✅ `src/components/news-card`
  - ✅ `src/pages/article-detail`
  - ✅ `src/styles/theme-variables`
  - ❌ `src/components/newsCard`
  - ❌ `src/pages/article_detail`
- Use snake_case for documentation files
  - ✅ `docs/dev/frontend_architecture.md`
  - ✅ `docs/api/endpoints.md`
  - ❌ `docs/dev/frontend-architecture.md`

### Component Naming
- Use PascalCase for React components
  - ✅ `NewsCard`
  - ✅ `ArticleDetail`
  - ❌ `news-card`
- Use camelCase for component files
  - ✅ `newsCard.tsx`
  - ✅ `articleDetail.tsx`
  - ❌ `news-card.tsx`

## Implementation Details

### Responsive Design
- Ensure that the interface is responsive across different devices and screen sizes
- Use media queries to adjust layout and content based on screen width

### Accessibility
- Implement proper ARIA attributes and semantic HTML
- Ensure keyboard accessibility and screen reader support

### Performance
- Optimize image sizes and use lazy loading for images
- Minimize network requests and use caching strategies

### Error Handling and Loading States
- Implement proper error handling and loading states for user feedback
- Use asynchronous programming to handle network requests and data loading

### Styling and Branding
- Maintain consistent styling and branding across the interface
- Use CSS variables and custom properties for reusable styles

### Component Reusability
- Design components with reusability in mind
- Use props and context to pass data and functionality between components

### Documentation
- Write clear and concise documentation for each component and file
- Use comments and code blocks to explain complex logic and functionality

## Conclusion

By following these rules and guidelines, you can create a high-quality, user-friendly, and maintainable frontend interface for the Naija News Hub. 